#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: origin/lilo.txt:40
msgid "Copying BMP -----------"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:47
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tYou can use any BMP with the dimensions 640x480 and a colordepth \n"
"        of 16Bit. If you decide to use one of the BMP's shipped with \n"
"        the lilo-package, you can find them at lilo-src/sample/ \n"
"        Just copy one of them to /boot (or somewhere else if \n"
"        you want to). Imho logo64a.bmp looks good so I will refer \n"
"        to this on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: origin/lilo.txt:51
msgid "Preparing lilo.conf -------------------"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "        There are two ways\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:56
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\ta) set the symlink /boot/boot.b to /boot/boot-bmp.b\n"
"        b) add install=boot/boot-bmp.b to lilo.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:59
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"        I prefer to change the symlink for several reasons, so you \n"
"        will find no install= in my lilo.conf below\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "        add the following lines to lilo.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "------------------------------------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:67
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"bitmap = /boot/logo64a.bmp (or whatever bmp you took)\n"
"bmp-colors = 6,9,0,15,9,0\n"
"bmp-table = 59,5,1,18,\n"
"bmp-timer = 66,28,6,8,0\n"
"-----------------------------------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:73
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"bmp-colors: here is where you set the colors used in your menu \n"
" the first three entries belongs to the normal menu-text and the\n"
" last three entries specifies the colors of the highlighted\n"
" menu-text.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:80
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"bmp-table: location of the menu-table. First two entries gives\n"
" the x, and y cooridiantes of the menu table. 59 means column 59, \n"
" you cal also use (eg) p400 to adress in pixels instead. The next\n"
" two entries are the numbers of the rows and columns in our menu table.\n"
" The last entry will specify the space between the columns if there are\n"
" more than one.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"bmp-timer: location of the timer-box for the countdown. The first two\n"
" entries are the coordinates and the next last values specifies  the colors  "
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:85
msgid ""
"alternatively, if you use a lilo version greater than 22.3 you could also "
"do:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:87
msgid "add the followjng lines to lilo.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "--------------------------------------------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:90
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"bitmap = /boot/logo64a.bmp (or whatever bmp you took)\n"
"-------------------------------------------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:97
msgid ""
"cat > /boot/logo64a.dat << \"EOF\" bmp-colors = 6,9,0,15,9,0 bmp-table = "
"59,5,1,18, bmp-timer = 66,28,6,8,0 EOF"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:99
msgid "lilo -E /boot/logo64a.dat"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:102
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(see the manpage and the README's shipped with your lilo-Source for\n"
" further details)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: origin/lilo.txt:106
msgid "Finish ------"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\trun lilo and reboot\n"
"\tEnjoy your new Boot-menu ;)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
#: origin/lilo.txt:112
msgid "Additional Remarks & Warnings -----------------------------"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lilo.txt:123
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tAs it can be very risky to use lilo you should always have a\n"
"    working boot disk to 'repair' your boot image if things went\n"
"    wrong, and it will go wrong for sure ;)\n"
"    Be sure, that your bmp-file exists and will not be erased\n"
"    accidently. \n"
"    And last not least : never forget to run lilo after you have\n"
"    made some changes.\n"
"\tThere are advantages and disadvantages which comes with \n"
"\tupgrading to lilo-22.3. Just check which is more important for \n"
"\tyou.\n"
msgstr ""

